cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for detecting adversarial examples in deep neural networks, which is a common problem in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves training robust models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
